title: Fingerprints don't match

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I just started a new project. I added `ndarray` as a dependency and when I tried to build I got this error. I had built the project with a different toolchain before I added `ndarray`. I switched to nightly because the git dependency requires it, but I get this error even when that is commented out in `Cargo.toml`. ### Code ```Rust fn main() { println!("Hello, world!"); } ``` In `Cargo.toml` ```toml [package] name = "onitama-alpha-zero" version = "0.1.0" authors = ["Viliam Vadocz "] edition = "2018" # See more keys and their definitions at https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/manifest.html [dependencies] # onitama_move_gen = { git = "https://github.com/LHolten/onitama" } ndarray = "0.15.1" ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`:
